# Dashboard Overhaul — Integration Guide

## File placement

```
application/
├── controllers/
│   └── Dashboard.php                          ← replace existing
├── models/
│   └── Dashboard_model.php                    ← replace existing
└── views/
    ├── dashboard/
    │   ├── index.php                           ← replace existing (staff)
    │   ├── admin_index.php                     ← NEW (admin/superadmin)
    │   └── widgets/
    │       ├── hr_kpi_strip.php                ← replace existing
    │       ├── staff_kpi_strip.php             ← NEW
    │       ├── headcount_widget.php            ← replace existing
    │       ├── dept_chart_widget.php           ← NEW
    │       ├── ticket_chart_widget.php         ← NEW
    │       │
    │       │   (keep your existing widgets unchanged):
    │       ├── calendar_widget.php
    │       ├── announcements_widget.php
    │       ├── birthdays_widget.php
    │       ├── todo_widget.php
    │       ├── team_widget.php
    │       └── my_open_tickets.php
    └── layouts/
        └── master.php                          ← no changes needed

assets/
├── css/
│   └── dashboard.css                          ← NEW, include in master layout
├── js/
│   └── dashboard.js                           ← NEW, include in master layout
└── vendor/
    └── sortablejs/
        └── Sortable.min.js                    ← NEW dependency (see below)
```

---

## New dependency: SortableJS

Download or install SortableJS for drag-and-drop:

```bash
# Option A — npm
npm install sortablejs
cp node_modules/sortablejs/Sortable.min.js assets/vendor/sortablejs/

# Option B — CDN (add to master layout)
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/sortablejs@1.15.2/Sortable.min.js"></script>
```

---

## Database migration

Run once:

```bash
mysql -u <user> -p <database> < application/sql/dashboard_schema.sql
```

---

## Widget view convention

Every widget view **must** stamp these attributes on its outermost element so
`dashboard.js` can discover it:

```php
<div class="card border-0 shadow-sm"
     data-widget-id="<?= Dashboard_model::generate_widget_id('my_widget', 'row3-col-1') ?>"
     data-container-id="row3-col-1"
     data-widget-label="My Widget">
    <!-- widget content -->
</div>
```

The `render_dashboard_widgets()` helper (your existing `dashboard_helper.php`)
should forward these attributes when it renders each widget. If you don't control
that helper, add the attributes manually inside each widget view file — wrap the
entire card output in a `<div data-widget-id="...">`.

---

## render_dashboard_widgets() signature change

The staff/admin views now pass a second argument (the container's saved prefs):

```php
render_dashboard_widgets($id, $widget_prefs[$id] ?? []);
```

Update your helper to accept and apply this:

```php
function render_dashboard_widgets(string $container_id, array $prefs = []): void {
    // existing registry lookup …
    $order      = $prefs['order']      ?? [];
    $visibility = $prefs['visibility'] ?? [];

    // sort by saved order if present
    if ($order) {
        usort($widgets, function ($a, $b) use ($order) {
            $ia = array_search($a['id'], $order);
            $ib = array_search($b['id'], $order);
            $ia = $ia === false ? PHP_INT_MAX : $ia;
            $ib = $ib === false ? PHP_INT_MAX : $ib;
            return $ia <=> $ib;
        });
    }

    foreach ($widgets as $w) {
        $visible = $visibility[$w['id']] ?? true;
        // still render (JS toggles display); hidden widgets load but are invisible
        CI::instance()->load->view($w['view']);
    }
}
```

---

## KPI query table assumptions

`Dashboard_model::get_admin_kpis()` queries these tables. Adjust names to match
your schema:

| Method variable     | Table assumed        | Column checked       |
|---------------------|----------------------|----------------------|
| headcount           | `users`              | `status = 'active'`  |
| new_hires           | `users`              | `created_at >= month_start` |
| open_tickets        | `support_tickets`    | `status IN (open, in_progress)` |
| resolved_tickets    | `support_tickets`    | `status = 'resolved'` |
| pending_leaves      | `leave_requests`     | `status = 'pending'` |
| attendance_today    | `attendance`         | `DATE(check_in) = today` |
| dept breakdown      | `users`              | `department` (GROUP BY) |

For staff KPIs, tasks are queried from a `tasks` table with `assigned_to` and
`due_date` columns. Adjust if your schema differs.

---

## What changed vs. original

| Area                    | Before                                      | After                                          |
|-------------------------|---------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| Role routing            | Both roles render same view                 | Separate `index.php` / `admin_index.php`       |
| Widget prefs table      | Stub model (no real DB)                     | `dashboard_widget_prefs` with JSON columns     |
| Drag-and-drop           | None                                        | SortableJS, persisted to DB                    |
| Visibility toggle       | Partial `save_visibility()`, no UI          | Manage panel + toggle pill UI + AJAX           |
| KPI data                | Hardcoded/missing                           | `get_admin_kpis()` + `get_staff_kpis()`        |
| KPI charts              | Only ApexCharts wired up loosely            | Dept donut + Ticket area + Headcount sparkline |
| KPI refresh             | None                                        | Manual button + 5-min auto-poll                |
| JS                      | None                                        | `dashboard.js` (~200 lines, no framework)      |
| CSS                     | None                                        | `dashboard.css` (drag states, KPI cards, dark) |
| `toggle_widget()`       | Missing                                     | New AJAX endpoint                              |
| `_json_ok/_json_error`  | Inline repeated code                        | DRY private helpers                            |